Comment.Paragraph: The composite cDNA library was made using mRNA extracted from setting and swelling buds harvested on 3 adult European ashes located in the Ciron Valley (France). The library was built using the CreatorTM SmartTM cDNA library construction kit (Clontech) according to the manufacturer's instructions.
Whole genomic DNA extracted from 2451S in 2013

Attributes.Attribute: Tree 2451(S), Rep1, Living ash collection at Earth Trust, Oxfordshire, UK

Comment.Paragraph: This is the parent of the tree used in the WGS study. We sequenced RNA from four tissues of this tree: root, leaf, cambium and flower.
